
Overview of verb sail

The verb sail has 4 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                           
1. (13) sail -- (traverse or travel on (a body of water); "We sailed the Atlantic"; "He sailed the Pacific all alone")
2. (3) sweep, sail -- (move with sweeping, effortless, gliding motions; "The diva swept into the room"; "Shreds of paper sailed through the air"; "The searchlights swept across the sky")
3. (1) sail -- (travel on water propelled by wind; "I love sailing, especially on the open sea"; "the ship sails on")
4. voyage, sail, navigate -- (travel on water propelled by wind or by other means; "The QE2 will sail to Southampton tomorrow")
